            <thetext>In version 0.6.6 the qx.ui.table.Table was focusable with the mouse.

The table got the focus by clicking on the pane, the scrollbar, the rows or the header.

The visual representation of the focused state is that the row has a blue background while when the focus is lost the row has a grey background.

This also means that attached key events are not routed to the table.

I usually attach a keypress event for &quot;enter&quot; and &quot;del&quot; to the table to allow the user editing and deleting of rows.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
